<bibRefCitation author="Li P. - C. &amp; Skvortsov A. K." box="[324,586,1824,1851]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="286 - 301" refId="ref37252" refString="Li P. - C. &amp; Skvortsov A. K. 1999. Betulaceae. In: Wu Z. Y. &amp; Raven P. H. (eds.) Flora of China 4: 286 - 301. Science Press, Beijing, and Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis." type="journal article" year="1999">Li &amp; Skvortsov 1999</bibRefCitation>
), 
<emphasis box="[610,817,1824,1850]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Flora Sichuanica</emphasis>
(Editorial 
<bibRefCitation author="Editorial Board of the Flora Sichuanica" box="[950,1386,1824,1851]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref34770" refString="Editorial Board of the Flora Sichuanica 2012. Flora Sichuanica. Vol. 21. Sichuan Publishing Group, Chengdu, China." type="book" year="2012">Board of the Flora Sichuanica 2012</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<emphasis box="[284,715,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">World Checklist and Bibliography of</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Govaerts &amp; Frodin 1998)" baseAuthorityName="Govaerts &amp; Frodin" baseAuthorityYear="1998" box="[722,1135,1860,1886]" class="Magnoliopsida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="order">
<emphasis box="[722,817,1860,1886]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fagales</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Govaerts R. &amp; Frodin D. G." box="[832,1126,1860,1886]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref35520" refString="Govaerts R. &amp; Frodin D. G. 1998. World Checklist and Bibliography of Fagales (Betulaceae, Corylaceae, Fagaceae and Ticodendraceae). The Royal Botanic Gardens Kew, England." type="book" year="1998">Govaerts &amp; Frodin 1998</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The specimen chosen as a 
<typeStatus box="[290,398,1895,1921]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">lectotype</typeStatus>
here bears two numbers: “no. 197” (with the number circled) and “no. 212.” There are different numbering systems in Delavay’s collections (
<bibRefCitation author="Holstein N. &amp; Weigend M." box="[916,1241,1930,1957]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="235 - 238" refId="ref36001" refString="Holstein N. &amp; Weigend M. 2016 a. An annotated checklist and lectotypification of Ostryopsis Decne. (Betulaceae), with notes on the numbering system in the collections of P. J. M. Delavay. Phytotaxa 282 (3): 235 - 238. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 282.3.9" type="journal article" year="2016">Holstein &amp; Weigend 2016a</bibRefCitation>
), and the 197 is Delavay’s original number. The number “212” is apparently the specimen number placed on the sheet at the Paris herbarium, which is also found on specimen P06811321.
</paragraph>
